---
title: "Borrowing power calculator"
description: "Estimate how much you could borrow for a home loan — including the 3% APRA assessment buffer and lender expense benchmarks most calculators quietly skip."
layout: base.njk
permalink: /calculators/borrowing-power/
---

{% block schema %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebApplication",
  "name": "Borrowing Power Calculator",
  "description": "{{ description }}",
  "url": "https://wombathomeloans.com.au/calculators/borrowing-power/",
  "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Web",
  "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "AUD" },
  "provider": { "@type": "MortgageBroker", "name": "Wombat Home Loans", "url": "https://wombathomeloans.com.au/" }
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

<section class="section section--tight">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="calc-breadcrumb"><a href="/calculators/">← All calculators</a></p>
    <span class="eyebrow">Borrowing power</span>
    <h1>How much would a lender <em>actually let me borrow?</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Most borrowing calculators flatter you. This one works the way a lender does — after-tax income, benchmark living expenses, your other commitments, and the 3% serviceability buffer on top of the interest rate. Fewer surprises later.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--cool section--tight" data-calc="borrowing">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="calc-grid">

      {# ── Inputs ── #}
      <div class="calc-card calc-panel">

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head"><label>Applicants</label></div>
          <div class="seg" id="b-applicants" role="group" aria-label="Number of applicants">
            <button type="button" data-value="1" aria-pressed="false">Just me</button>
            <button type="button" data-value="2" aria-pressed="true">Two of us</button>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-inc1-input">Your income (gross, per year)</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="b-inc1-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Applicant one gross annual income">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-inc1" type="range" min="0" max="500000" step="5000" value="150000" aria-label="Applicant one income slider">
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field" id="b-inc2-wrap">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-inc2-input">Second income (gross, per year)</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="b-inc2-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Applicant two gross annual income">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-inc2" type="range" min="0" max="500000" step="5000" value="100000" aria-label="Applicant two income slider">
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-rental-input">Rental income (per year, if any)</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="b-rental-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Annual rental income">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-rental" type="range" min="0" max="150000" step="1000" value="0" aria-label="Rental income slider">
          <p class="calc-field__hint">Lenders only count about 80% of rent, to allow for vacancies and costs — we do the same.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-deps">Dependants</label>
            <span class="calc-field__value" id="b-deps-out"></span>
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-deps" type="range" min="0" max="5" step="1" value="0">
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-expenses-input">Living expenses (per month)</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="b-expenses-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Monthly living expenses">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-expenses" type="range" min="1000" max="15000" step="100" value="4000" aria-label="Living expenses slider">
          <p class="calc-field__hint" id="b-hem-note"></p>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-debts-input">Other loan repayments (per month)</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="b-debts-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Other monthly loan repayments">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-debts" type="range" min="0" max="10000" step="50" value="0" aria-label="Other loan repayments slider">
          <p class="calc-field__hint">Car loans, personal loans, HECS repayments — anything that leaves your account monthly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-cc-input">Credit card limits (total)</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="b-cc-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Total credit card limits">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-cc" type="range" min="0" max="100000" step="1000" value="10000" aria-label="Credit card limits slider">
          <p class="calc-field__hint">Lenders assess the <em>limit</em>, not the balance — even if you pay it off in full every month. A $20k limit you never use still shrinks your borrowing power.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-rate">Interest rate</label>
            <span class="calc-field__value" id="b-rate-out"></span>
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-rate" type="range" min="4" max="9" step="0.05" value="5.75">
          <p class="calc-field__hint">Lenders test you at this rate <strong>plus 3%</strong> — the APRA serviceability buffer. We apply it automatically.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-field">
          <div class="calc-field__head">
            <label for="b-deposit-input">Your deposit</label>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-affix">
            <input class="calc-input" id="b-deposit-input" type="text" inputmode="numeric" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Deposit amount">
          </div>
          <input class="calc-range" id="b-deposit" type="range" min="0" max="1000000" step="10000" value="200000" aria-label="Deposit slider">
        </div>

      </div>

      {# ── Results ── #}
      <div class="stack-lg">

        <div class="calc-card">
          <div class="calc-hero-stat">
            <span class="calc-hero-stat__label">Estimated borrowing power</span>
            <span class="calc-hero-stat__value" id="b-hero">$0</span>
            <p class="calc-hero-stat__note" id="b-hero-note"></p>
          </div>
          <div class="calc-stats">
            <div class="calc-stat">
              <span class="calc-stat__label">Property budget (loan + deposit)</span>
              <span class="calc-stat__value" id="b-stat-budget">$0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-stat">
              <span class="calc-stat__label">Monthly repayment at your rate</span>
              <span class="calc-stat__value" id="b-stat-repay">$0</span>
            </div>
            <div class="calc-stat">
              <span class="calc-stat__label">Assessment rate used</span>
              <span class="calc-stat__value" id="b-stat-assess">0%</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="calc-field__hint" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">Budget excludes stamp duty and purchase costs — set aside roughly 4–5% of the price for those.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-card">
          <h3>Where your monthly income goes</h3>
          <p class="calc-field__hint" style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);">This is your household's monthly income, sliced the way a lender's servicing calculator slices it. The navy segment is what's left to service a loan.</p>
          <div class="calc-chart calc-chart--short" style="max-width: 420px; margin-inline: auto;"><canvas id="b-chart-split" role="img" aria-label="Doughnut chart of monthly income allocation across tax, living expenses, commitments and loan capacity"></canvas></div>
        </div>

        <div class="calc-card">
          <h3>How rates move your number</h3>
          <p class="calc-field__hint" style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);">Your borrowing power isn't a fixed number — every rate move re-draws it. This is why pre-approvals go stale and why timing matters.</p>
          <div class="calc-chart"><canvas id="b-chart-sens" role="img" aria-label="Line chart of estimated borrowing power across a range of interest rates"></canvas></div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-assumptions" data-reveal>
      <details>
        <summary>Assumptions behind this calculator</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Income is taxed at 2025–26 Australian resident rates including the Medicare levy and low income tax offset; HECS/HELP and other offsets aren't modelled.</li>
          <li>Living expenses use the higher of your figure and a simplified household benchmark (as lenders do with HEM).</li>
          <li>Credit cards are assessed at 3.8% of the total limit per month; rental income is shaded to 80%.</li>
          <li>The loan is assessed over 30 years at your rate plus a 3% buffer, principal &amp; interest.</li>
          <li>Real lenders differ enormously — especially with bonus income, RSUs, foreign income and self-employment. That's the gap a broker closes.</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% include "calc-cta.njk" %}

